snippet.title: Mustache In The Wind
snippet.description: The Southern Reticulated Mustache is not a pack mustache like other breeds. It is raised by the mother for about 3-4 months in the wild before she abandons it to fend for itself. At first, its attempts to feed off of adult upper lips for sweat and gristle are clumsy, and the mustache is easily swatted away. It must either learn confidence or perish on the sidewalk, consigned to an existence spent propelled by the cold sharp breeze with no stability, hot nose breath or sandwich crumbs to keep it alive.

snippet.title: A Betting Man
snippet.description: Jimmy "Bets Entirely Too Much" Pocobean was known as A Betting Man, that drunken nouveau riche billionaire in every tight-knit community who drives away his wife and kids under the delusion that God loves to give him money. His hirsute golfing buddy that day, who claimed to be a well-adjusted salesperson stopping through town, was actually none other than Terrence Hildebrand, a conniving confidence man who had a knack for getting rich people into space without a way back. Once Pocobean foolishly achieved escape velocity, Hildebrand strolled into his palatial estate and proceeded to leisurely rob it over the course of the next 25 years.

snippet.title: Intimacy Bat

Sometimes a bat to the face also says "I'm going to kill you because you didn't give me your wallet as promptly as I would have liked," but even then there's a certain level of intimacy to that statement that a bat to the face only amplifies.

Right before they die, the last drink they offer you with their trembling old man hands is as good as the gin gets. That's really when it's at its smoothest.

snippet.title: Sherlock Holmes: The Mystery Of The Ant Killer

It was, indeed the curious incident of the ant in the day-time.
